    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-07-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Plumb</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 76.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-07-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 15, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to inclose to you a copy of a
                    communication received from T. W. Scott, consul at Matainoras, in reference to
                    the seizure of an amount of gold coin by the custom-house authorities at that
                    port, belonging to Dr. W. L. Huchinson. a citizen of the United States.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to make an investigation of this case and report to this
                    department.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward L. Plumb</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
